ill goes on in Texas, the lifeways described here have nearly vanished as the state has become highly urbanized. Thus, this book preserves a fascinating record of an important part of Texas' rural heritage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCotton farmerszTexaszFayette County. 0aCotton farmerszTexaszWashington County. 0aEthnologyzTexaszFayette County. 0aEthnologyzTexaszWashington County. 0aFarm lifezTexaszFayette County. 0aFarm lifezTexaszWashington County. 0aOral history. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aUtley, Dan K., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/77720040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292799875423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292799875/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK